Vice President Biden spoke with President Poroshenko of Ukraine, expressing concern over the recent increase in fighting in eastern Ukraine. Both leaders emphasized the importance of a political and diplomatic solution to the conflict through the implementation of the Minsk agreements. The Vice President conveyed that the United States has sent a message to Russia, urging them to deescalate the situation. He also advised Ukraine to show restraint. The leaders also discussed progress in meeting IMF conditions for financial assistance and acknowledged the significance of anti-corruption reforms in Ukraine.